From d57db4f3758a1e7487c660ae2a377a7902cd9e6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 17:21:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add gen-seq-error-model subcommand

Adds a new CLI subcommand that reads a FASTQ file, accumulates
per-position quality-score transition counts and a global error rate,
then writes a SequencingErrorModel (with an embedded QualityScoreModel)
to disk. Mirrors the Python NEAT model_sequencing_error algorithm.

Also fixes two pre-existing compile errors in fastq_tools.rs: missing
QualityScoreModel import and a redundant quality_score_model parameter
in write_block_fastq whose callers had already dropped it.

https://claude.ai/code/session_0145gMaN94vH3vnxripbBvBZ
